1
00:00:02.127 --> 00:00:03.837  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
<i>[narrator]</i>
<i>Last time on</i> Star Trek Voyager...

2
00:00:04.963 --> 00:00:06.590  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
I believe we know each other.

3
00:00:06.673 --> 00:00:09.676  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
You're Tuvok, right?
We met last week at the shift briefing.

4
00:00:09.760 --> 00:00:12.638  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
Before that.
Before we were working here.

5
00:00:12.721 --> 00:00:14.097  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Oh, I don't think so.

6
00:00:14.181 --> 00:00:17.518  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
A romantic relationship is really
out of the question for me right now,

7
00:00:17.601 --> 00:00:19.061  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
-and when you started asking...
-How about a friend?

8
00:00:19.144 --> 00:00:20.145  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
What?

9
00:00:20.812 --> 00:00:22.064  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Could you use a friend?

10
00:00:22.147 --> 00:00:24.983  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
It's nice to be in a place where
different species get along so well.

11
00:00:25.067 --> 00:00:26.610  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
Oh, so you admit
we're getting along?

12
00:00:27.152 --> 00:00:28.946  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
-[Kim]<i> Kim to Chakotay.</i>
-[Chakotay]<i> Go ahead.</i>

13
00:00:29.029 --> 00:00:30.364  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
I've found them, Commander.

14
00:00:30.447 --> 00:00:32.282  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
-Let go of me!
-I'm not going to hurt you.

15
00:00:32.366 --> 00:00:33.617  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
[grunting]

16
00:00:33.700 --> 00:00:34.701  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
[screams]

17
00:00:35.661 --> 00:00:37.120  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
No! No!

18
00:00:38.664 --> 00:00:40.457  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
Harry, I need
an emergency transport now!

19
00:00:46.129 --> 00:00:47.130  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
No, leave me alone!

20
00:00:47.214 --> 00:00:49.258  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
We're friends.
We're trying to help you.

21
00:00:49.341 --> 00:00:50.634  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
No, don't touch me!

22
00:00:50.717 --> 00:00:53.512  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
I don't believe you are
who you think you are!

23
00:00:54.680 --> 00:00:56.473  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
[Tuvok] We don't belong here.

24
00:00:56.557 --> 00:00:58.100  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
This isn't right!

25
00:00:58.183 --> 00:00:59.685  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
We don't belong here!

26
00:00:59.768 --> 00:01:01.728  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
[narrator]<i> And now the conclusion.</i>

27
00:01:09.611 --> 00:01:11.488  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
-[man] Wait here.
-Yes, sir.

28
00:01:38.932 --> 00:01:41.268  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
He's deactivated a safety field.

29
00:01:44.605 --> 00:01:46.523  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
-[beeping]
-Alert Emergency Medical.

30
00:01:46.607 --> 00:01:48.567  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
He may have tried to ju...
[grunting]

31
00:01:59.953 --> 00:02:00.954  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
[groans]

32
00:02:17.888 --> 00:02:19.514  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
I can't penetrate their shields.

33
00:02:21.183 --> 00:02:22.893  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Maybe we don't have to.

34
00:02:24.353 --> 00:02:25.604  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
The Battle of Vorkado.

35
00:02:25.687 --> 00:02:27.481  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
It's in my tactical database.

36
00:02:27.564 --> 00:02:30.067  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
A Romulan captain
disabled two attacking vessels

37
00:02:30.150 --> 00:02:32.944  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
by creating a photonic shock wave
between the ships.

38
00:02:33.028 --> 00:02:34.112  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
How'd he do that?

39
00:02:34.196 --> 00:02:35.781  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Watch and learn.

40
00:02:42.829 --> 00:02:45.457  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
I don't think they'll be
bothering us again.

41
00:02:45.540 --> 00:02:47.959  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
Good work.
Let's go back for Chakotay.

42
00:02:48.960 --> 00:02:51.421  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
Five more ships
on an intercept course.

43
00:02:51.505 --> 00:02:53.840  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
What's your tactical database
telling you now?

44
00:02:54.633 --> 00:02:58.303  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
Transporters are damaged.
Shields are failing.

45
00:02:58.387 --> 00:02:59.888  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
We have to retreat,
come up with a new plan.

46
00:02:59.971 --> 00:03:01.473  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Agreed.

47
00:03:01.556 --> 00:03:03.809  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
[indistinct chatter]

48
00:03:26.415 --> 00:03:28.207  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Listen, I'm sorry about my friend.

49
00:03:29.208 --> 00:03:31.210  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
-Excuse me?
-Jaffen.

50
00:03:31.837 --> 00:03:34.131  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
He wasn't very nice
when I invited you to join us.

51
00:03:37.008 --> 00:03:38.468  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Are you all right?

52
00:03:39.511 --> 00:03:41.221  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
I'm just a little tired.

53
00:03:41.304 --> 00:03:42.431  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
First day on a new job.

54
00:03:42.514 --> 00:03:44.558  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
I know how that can be.

55
00:03:44.641 --> 00:03:47.310  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
Well, I just wanted to let you know
you're more than welcome to sit with us.

56
00:03:47.394 --> 00:03:50.105  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
Actually, I was thinking
about going home.

57
00:03:50.188 --> 00:03:53.817  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
Well, if you change your mind,
we're celebrating.

58
00:03:54.568 --> 00:03:55.652  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
What's the occasion?

59
00:03:55.736 --> 00:03:57.738  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
I've decided
to move in with Jaffen.

60
00:04:00.073 --> 00:04:01.324  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Congratulations.

61
00:05:59.234 --> 00:06:01.027  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:10.00% 
Look among the patrons.

62
00:06:13.957 --> 00:06:16.418  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Yerid, Criminal Investigations.

63
00:06:16.501 --> 00:06:19.337  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
[scoffs]
We run an honest business.

64
00:06:19.421 --> 00:06:21.548  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:10.00% 
I'm looking for two people
who disappeared

65
00:06:21.631 --> 00:06:25.093  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:10.00% 
after leaving here earlier this evening.
One was a young pregnant woman...

66
00:06:25.176 --> 00:06:26.261  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
B'Elanna?

67
00:06:26.344 --> 00:06:27.512  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
You know her?

68
00:06:27.596 --> 00:06:31.057  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:10.00% 
Oh, I knew I should have
walked her to the Transport.

69
00:06:31.141 --> 00:06:33.685  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
Why, did you think someone
might try to hurt her?

70
00:06:33.768 --> 00:06:35.645  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
The city is supposed
to be safe.

71
00:06:36.146 --> 00:06:38.356  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
The person with her
was described as short

72
00:06:38.440 --> 00:06:40.525  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:10.00% 
with mottled skin,
facial hair...

73
00:06:40.609 --> 00:06:42.652  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:10.00% 
Sounds like someone
who was in here earlier,

74
00:06:42.736 --> 00:06:45.196  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:10.00% 
-a worker from the plant.
-Do you know his name?

75
00:06:45.280 --> 00:06:46.615  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:10.00% 
Uh...

76
00:06:48.074 --> 00:06:50.201  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:10.00% 
Neelix, I think.

77
00:06:50.285 --> 00:06:52.162  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
Did you see him talking to anyone else
while he was here?

78
00:06:52.245 --> 00:06:55.999  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:10.00% 
He had a friend.
Uh, Amal something.

79
00:06:56.082 --> 00:06:58.376  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
-Can you describe him?
-Oh, I don't have to.

80
00:06:58.460 --> 00:06:59.586  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
He's sitting right over...

81
00:07:05.133 --> 00:07:09.346  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:10.00% 
[Doctor]<i> ECH Log,</i>
<i>Stardate 54622.4.</i>

82
00:07:09.428 --> 00:07:12.974  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
<i>I've found an ingenious place</i>
<i>to hide while we make repairs--</i>

83
00:07:13.058 --> 00:07:17.395  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
<i>a moon with a paramagnetic core</i>
<i>that masks our energy signature.</i>

84
00:07:17.479 --> 00:07:19.189  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
<i>I've turned my attention</i>
<i>to Lieutenant Torres,</i>

85
00:07:19.272 --> 00:07:22.734  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:10.00% 
<i>whose treatment</i>
<i>will also require ingenuity.</i>

86
00:07:23.610 --> 00:07:26.863  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:10.00% 
The scan on the left was performed
during B'Elanna's last physical.

87
00:07:26.947 --> 00:07:29.157  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:10.00% 
The one on the right,
just a few minutes ago.

88
00:07:29.240 --> 00:07:33.370  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:10.00% 
The memory centers of her brain
have been radically altered.

89
00:07:33.453 --> 00:07:35.538  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
People from our crew
seemed to remember

90
00:07:35.622 --> 00:07:37.540  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
parts of their real lives,

91
00:07:37.624 --> 00:07:40.126  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:10.00% 
but they got a lot
of the details wrong.

92
00:07:40.210 --> 00:07:43.630  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:10.00% 
Tom knew his name,
that he was from Earth,

93
00:07:43.713 --> 00:07:47.092  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:10.00% 
but he said space travel
made him sick.

94
00:07:47.175 --> 00:07:50.095  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:10.00% 
Whoever did this
is very sophisticated,

95
00:07:50.178 --> 00:07:53.264  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:10.00% 
capable of selectively
manipulating memory engrams.

96
00:07:53.348 --> 00:07:55.892  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:10.00% 
Some have been suppressed,
some altered,

97
00:07:55.976 --> 00:07:57.686  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:10.00% 
others left intact.

98
00:07:57.769 --> 00:07:59.229  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:10.00% 
Can you undo the damage?

99
00:07:59.312 --> 00:08:03.066  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:10.00% 
I believe so,
but it'll take some time.

100
00:08:03.149 --> 00:08:05.443  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
I wish I could help.

101
00:08:05.527 --> 00:08:06.945  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:10.00% 
Maybe you can.

102
00:08:07.028 --> 00:08:08.863  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:10.00% 
She'll require several treatments.

103
00:08:08.947 --> 00:08:12.075  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
In between, you could expose her
to familiar sights and surroundings.

104
00:08:12.158 --> 00:08:13.618  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Say no more.

105
00:08:13.702 --> 00:08:17.122  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
I'll take her on a whirlwind tour
of her own life.

106
00:08:17.205 --> 00:08:18.331  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Don't rush things.

107
00:08:18.415 --> 00:08:21.710  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
This is going to be
very traumatic for her.

108
00:08:24.754 --> 00:08:27.424  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
[man] Acute anxiety, depression...

109
00:08:27.507 --> 00:08:30.427  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
When I interviewed him, he insisted
that he's not who he's supposed to be

110
00:08:30.510 --> 00:08:34.264  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
that we've... "stolen his katra,"
whatever that is.

111
00:08:34.347 --> 00:08:36.766  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Conclusions?

112
00:08:36.850 --> 00:08:39.978  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
Tri-lobe regression complex?
Polar-affective disorder?

113
00:08:40.061 --> 00:08:43.440  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
Neuropsychiatry isn't
a guessing game, Dr. Ravoc.

114
00:08:44.691 --> 00:08:45.900  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Dysphoria Syndrome.

115
00:08:46.901 --> 00:08:49.154  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
You have been studying my research.

116
00:08:49.237 --> 00:08:51.281  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
According to your work,
the condition is very rare.

117
00:08:51.364 --> 00:08:54.743  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
It is.
I've treated this man before.

118
00:08:54.826 --> 00:08:57.328  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
Apparently,
he's suffered a relapse.

119
00:08:57.412 --> 00:08:59.164  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Recommended treatment?

120
00:08:59.247 --> 00:09:02.292  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
Engramatic resequencing
is typically indicated.

121
00:09:02.375 --> 00:09:03.543  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
You seem skeptical.

122
00:09:04.669 --> 00:09:06.713  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Resequencing is a radical procedure.

123
00:09:06.796 --> 00:09:10.300  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
If he had a malignant tumor,
would you be afraid to cut it out?

124
00:09:11.426 --> 00:09:12.510  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
No.

125
00:09:12.594 --> 00:09:16.890  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
This syndrome is just as insidious.
It requires aggressive treatment.

126
00:09:16.973 --> 00:09:17.974  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Get started.

127
00:09:27.692 --> 00:09:30.278  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Please... help me.

128
00:09:34.032 --> 00:09:35.825  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
That's what we're here to do.

129
00:09:53.301 --> 00:09:56.054  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
I want to know the status
of Employee 8583.

130
00:09:56.888 --> 00:09:59.099  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
Maybe it's different
where you come from,

131
00:09:59.182 --> 00:10:01.518  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
but here it's polite
to say "Good morning."

132
00:10:01.601 --> 00:10:03.144  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Good morning.

133
00:10:07.315 --> 00:10:11.903  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
8583, the man who was removed
by Security yesterday.

134
00:10:11.986 --> 00:10:13.488  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
He's been hospitalized.

135
00:10:14.489 --> 00:10:17.909  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
Is there any reason to believe
that his condition might be contagious?

136
00:10:17.992 --> 00:10:20.078  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
He came in contact
with other workers.

137
00:10:20.161 --> 00:10:22.080  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
Some of them
have expressed concern.

138
00:10:22.163 --> 00:10:23.915  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Well, tell them not to worry.

139
00:10:24.749 --> 00:10:26.543  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
Excuse me.
Am I intruding?

140
00:10:26.626 --> 00:10:28.002  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
What can we do for you?

141
00:10:28.086 --> 00:10:31.673  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
I'm investigating the disappearance
of two of your employees.

142
00:10:31.756 --> 00:10:34.968  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
-Who?
-Their names are Neelix and Torres.

143
00:10:35.051 --> 00:10:37.262  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
Both of them failed
to report for work today.

144
00:10:37.345 --> 00:10:39.639  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
What about this man?

145
00:10:42.225 --> 00:10:45.854  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
Employee 9363. He didn't report
for his shift either.

146
00:10:47.188 --> 00:10:49.023  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
I'd like to see
his personnel file,

147
00:10:49.107 --> 00:10:52.235  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
and I'll need to interview anyone
who may know where he is.

148
00:10:52.318 --> 00:10:53.736  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Why are you looking for him?

149
00:10:53.820 --> 00:10:55.780  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
I believe he's responsible
for the disappearance

150
00:10:55.864 --> 00:10:57.448  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
of the other two.

151
00:11:00.493 --> 00:11:02.745  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
You've only been here three weeks.

152
00:11:02.829 --> 00:11:06.040  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
-Where did you get all these things?
-I'm a collector.

153
00:11:07.500 --> 00:11:11.337  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
You collect spent plasma relays?

154
00:11:11.421 --> 00:11:15.008  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
I like to think of it
as a decorative object.

155
00:11:20.305 --> 00:11:21.848  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
You know...

156
00:11:23.308 --> 00:11:26.311  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
I think this would
look better over there.

157
00:11:26.394 --> 00:11:28.730  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
You're not going to start telling me
how to dress, are you?

158
00:11:28.813 --> 00:11:31.065  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
-[chuckles]
-Where are you going?

159
00:11:31.149 --> 00:11:33.234  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
To get the rest of my things.

160
00:11:33.318 --> 00:11:35.236  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
There's more?

161
00:12:01.888 --> 00:12:03.389  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Lights.

162
00:12:19.530 --> 00:12:21.407  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
What do you want?

163
00:12:21.491 --> 00:12:23.993  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
You told me you were moving out.

164
00:12:36.631 --> 00:12:38.757  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
I needed a place to hide.

165
00:12:39.634 --> 00:12:43.221  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
Jaffen knows where I am.
He'll come looking for me.

166
00:12:43.304 --> 00:12:46.057  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
I'm hoping you won't tell him I'm here.

167
00:12:48.142 --> 00:12:50.061  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
They say you had something to do

168
00:12:50.144 --> 00:12:52.855  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
with the disappearance
of a woman at the plant.

169
00:12:55.108 --> 00:12:58.528  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
I did.
Her name's B'Elanna.

170
00:12:58.611 --> 00:13:00.947  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
She was brought to this planet
against her will.

171
00:13:01.030 --> 00:13:04.200  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
Something was done to her
so she'd forget her real life.

172
00:13:04.284 --> 00:13:06.953  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
And what,
you helped her get home?

173
00:13:07.036 --> 00:13:08.162  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
That's right.

174
00:13:09.706 --> 00:13:12.917  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
There are other people in this city
who I'm also trying to help.

175
00:13:14.127 --> 00:13:16.546  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
I'm not here to hurt anyone.

176
00:13:16.629 --> 00:13:18.047  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
You have to trust me.

177
00:13:18.131 --> 00:13:20.425  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
You're pointing a weapon at me.

178
00:13:30.643 --> 00:13:33.438  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Go ahead. Report me.

179
00:13:33.521 --> 00:13:35.481  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
But if you do,

180
00:13:35.565 --> 00:13:37.859  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
a lot of innocent people
are going to suffer.

181
00:13:38.817 --> 00:13:42.697  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
All I'm asking for is a place to stay
until my friends come back for me.

182
00:13:49.662 --> 00:13:52.290  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
We're going to have to do
something about that arm.

183
00:13:56.669 --> 00:13:59.922  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
[Torres] The waiter...
from the tavern.

184
00:14:00.006 --> 00:14:02.717  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
Lieutenant Tom Paris,
our pilot,

185
00:14:02.800 --> 00:14:05.844  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
and B'Elanna Torres,
our Chief Engineer.

186
00:14:05.928 --> 00:14:08.222  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
That picture was taken
on your honeymoon.

187
00:14:09.766 --> 00:14:11.850  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
It isn't possible.

188
00:14:11.934 --> 00:14:13.728  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
How else would we have it?

189
00:14:21.110 --> 00:14:23.863  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
It's an antique television.

190
00:14:23.946 --> 00:14:26.032  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
You gave it to Tom as a present.

191
00:14:27.492 --> 00:14:30.870  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
-He watches cartoons.
-Yes.

192
00:14:32.830 --> 00:14:34.874  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
How do I know that?

193
00:14:34.957 --> 00:14:37.001  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Because you're starting to remember.

194
00:14:55.269 --> 00:14:58.106  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
I wondered why he was
so protective of me.

195
00:15:01.567 --> 00:15:03.903  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
I'll be outside if you need me.

196
00:15:30.304 --> 00:15:33.391  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Your shift ended three hours ago.

197
00:15:33.474 --> 00:15:38.312  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
My friend Jaffen,
Employee 1326-- he cut himself.

198
00:15:38.396 --> 00:15:40.773  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
Removing property from these premises
is not permitted.

199
00:15:40.857 --> 00:15:44.277  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
I know, but he's just too stubborn
to go to the hospital.

200
00:15:45.361 --> 00:15:47.989  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
I promise I'll have it back
first thing in the morning.

201
00:15:49.115 --> 00:15:50.491  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Be sure that you do.

202
00:16:05.715 --> 00:16:09.635  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
Display the personnel file
for Employee 8583.

203
00:16:09.719 --> 00:16:10.845  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
[Computer]<i> Access restricted.</i>

204
00:16:11.429 --> 00:16:13.389  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
<i>Security clearance verified.</i>

205
00:16:17.393 --> 00:16:21.689  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
Display all medical and historical data
for this employee's species.

206
00:16:21.772 --> 00:16:23.232  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
[beeping]
<i>Data unavailable.</i>

207
00:16:24.817 --> 00:16:28.321  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
List all files accessed
by this employee since he's been here.

208
00:16:28.404 --> 00:16:29.822  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
<i>Personnel files.</i>

209
00:16:29.906 --> 00:16:33.743  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
<i>Employee 8582</i>
<i>Nozawa, Kashimuro.</i>

210
00:16:34.327 --> 00:16:37.663  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
<i>Employee 8584</i>
<i>Janeway, Kathryn.</i>

211
00:16:37.747 --> 00:16:40.958  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
<i>Employee 8585</i>
<i>McKenzie, William.</i>

212
00:16:41.042 --> 00:16:44.295  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
<i>Employee 8586</i>
<i>Hansen, Annika.</i>

213
00:16:44.378 --> 00:16:47.673  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
<i>Employee 8587</i>
<i>Anderson, Lydia.</i>

214
00:16:47.757 --> 00:16:51.177  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
<i>Employee 8588</i>
<i>Torres, B'Elanna. Employee...</i>

215
00:16:52.970 --> 00:16:54.680  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
You need a doctor.

216
00:16:56.766 --> 00:16:59.060  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
It'll have to wait
till I'm back on<i> Voyager.</i>

217
00:17:00.770 --> 00:17:01.812  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
<i>Voyager?</i>

218
00:17:02.730 --> 00:17:04.106  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
My ship.

219
00:17:04.190 --> 00:17:05.983  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
You live onboard?

220
00:17:07.818 --> 00:17:10.279  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
For almost seven years.

221
00:17:10.363 --> 00:17:12.740  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
Don't you ever want
to stay in one place?

222
00:17:18.621 --> 00:17:21.165  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
You seem happy here.

223
00:17:21.249 --> 00:17:23.459  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
I've got a good job.

224
00:17:23.543 --> 00:17:25.711  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
Ever consider doing something
more challenging?

225
00:17:25.795 --> 00:17:28.506  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
My job's challenging enough.

226
00:17:28.589 --> 00:17:32.218  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
You monitor reactor coils, right?

227
00:17:32.301 --> 00:17:34.762  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
You're obviously
a very capable woman.

228
00:17:34.845 --> 00:17:36.806  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
You could probably run
that power plant.

229
00:17:36.889 --> 00:17:39.517  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
Why would I want
all that responsibility?

230
00:17:39.600 --> 00:17:41.477  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
[com chirps]

231
00:17:41.561 --> 00:17:42.728  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
What's that?

232
00:17:43.813 --> 00:17:45.731  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
My people are trying
to contact me.

233
00:17:47.358 --> 00:17:48.442  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Chakotay here.

234
00:17:48.526 --> 00:17:50.361  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
[Kim]<i> Are you okay, Commander?</i>

235
00:17:50.444 --> 00:17:52.655  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
For the time being.
Can you get me out of here?

236
00:17:52.738 --> 00:17:53.823  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
<i>No, sir.</i>

237
00:17:53.906 --> 00:17:55.575  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
We're eight light-years away.

238
00:17:55.658 --> 00:17:58.494  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
[Chakotay]<i> How are you transmitting</i>
<i>a signal that far?</i>

239
00:17:58.578 --> 00:18:00.288  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
We're using a triaxilating frequency

240
00:18:00.371 --> 00:18:02.540  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
on a covariant subspace band.

241
00:18:02.623 --> 00:18:04.208  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
<i>It was B'Elanna's idea.</i>

242
00:18:05.084 --> 00:18:07.503  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
I take it she's feeling better.

243
00:18:07.587 --> 00:18:09.463  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
<i>She's responded well to treatment.</i>

244
00:18:09.547 --> 00:18:11.591  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
<i>Have you located anyone else</i>
<i>from the crew?</i>

245
00:18:11.674 --> 00:18:15.886  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
As a matter of fact, I'm sitting
with Captain Janeway right now.

246
00:18:16.762 --> 00:18:19.890  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
<i>-How is she?</i>
-A little suspicious,

247
00:18:19.974 --> 00:18:22.101  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
just like B'Elanna was at first.

248
00:18:22.184 --> 00:18:24.937  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
How soon can you get back
into transporter range?

249
00:18:25.021 --> 00:18:26.897  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
We'll need a couple more days
to finish repairs.

250
00:18:26.981 --> 00:18:28.399  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
What about the shield grid?

251
00:18:28.482 --> 00:18:30.067  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
<i>I have an idea</i>
<i>how to shut it down.</i>

252
00:18:30.151 --> 00:18:33.988  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
Until I get back to you,
let's maintain com silence,

253
00:18:34.071 --> 00:18:36.032  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
just in case we're being monitored.

254
00:18:36.115 --> 00:18:38.451  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
<i>Understood.</i>
<i>Good luck, Commander.</i>

255
00:18:39.702 --> 00:18:41.412  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Why did you call me "Captain"?

256
00:18:43.205 --> 00:18:44.874  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Because that's who you are.

257
00:18:44.957 --> 00:18:46.792  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
That's absurd.

258
00:18:47.710 --> 00:18:49.462  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
So what are you saying?

259
00:18:49.545 --> 00:18:52.256  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
That I was brought here by force, too?
That my memories were manipulated?

260
00:18:52.340 --> 00:18:55.718  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
-I know it sounds strange, but...
-Helping you was a mistake.

261
00:18:57.928 --> 00:18:59.096  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Listen to me.

262
00:19:00.681 --> 00:19:02.600  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
There are more than a hundred
members of<i> Voyager's</i> crew

263
00:19:02.683 --> 00:19:05.102  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
working at that power plant--
your crew.

264
00:19:05.895 --> 00:19:08.606  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
And when our ship gets here,
I'll be able to prove it to you.

265
00:19:08.689 --> 00:19:10.441  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Look...

266
00:19:11.942 --> 00:19:14.654  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
I don't want to force you to do
anything you don't want to,

267
00:19:14.737 --> 00:19:16.572  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
but don't you at least want
to know the truth?

268
00:19:17.615 --> 00:19:19.158  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Let me prove who I am.

269
00:19:19.241 --> 00:19:21.369  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Hand me that dermal regenerator.

270
00:19:43.724 --> 00:19:45.226  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
We're the same race.

271
00:19:49.855 --> 00:19:51.857  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
We're more than that.

272
00:19:51.941 --> 00:19:53.484  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
We're friends.

273
00:20:00.032 --> 00:20:02.118  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Am I hearing you correctly?

274
00:20:02.201 --> 00:20:04.328  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
You're actually helping this man?

275
00:20:08.207 --> 00:20:10.668  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
He abducted one of the workers.

276
00:20:10.751 --> 00:20:12.628  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
She's a member of his crew.

277
00:20:12.712 --> 00:20:15.423  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Right, and you're the Captain.

278
00:20:16.382 --> 00:20:19.093  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
Don't you see?
He's trying to convince you

279
00:20:19.176 --> 00:20:22.555  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
that you'll have a better life
if you go with him.

280
00:20:22.638 --> 00:20:24.557  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Do you want to go with him?

281
00:20:25.850 --> 00:20:26.934  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
No.

282
00:20:27.017 --> 00:20:31.063  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
Then why are you risking
everything we have?

283
00:20:36.235 --> 00:20:38.154  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
-[door opens]
-I was starting to think...

284
00:20:39.238 --> 00:20:40.406  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Stay where you are.

285
00:20:41.699 --> 00:20:42.700  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
[shouts]

286
00:20:52.126 --> 00:20:53.252  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
[Chakotay] I don't know them.

287
00:20:53.335 --> 00:20:55.379  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
I think you do,

288
00:20:55.463 --> 00:20:58.424  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
and I think you were involved
in their disappearance.

289
00:20:58.507 --> 00:20:59.717  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
[sighs]

290
00:20:59.800 --> 00:21:02.511  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
I'm not the man you're looking for.

291
00:21:02.595 --> 00:21:05.139  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
Yes, the witness' description
doesn't fit you exactly,

292
00:21:05.222 --> 00:21:07.099  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
but I'm sure that'll be explained
once the doctor here

293
00:21:07.183 --> 00:21:10.436  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
finds evidence of dermal regeneration.

294
00:21:12.354 --> 00:21:13.814  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
What is it?

295
00:21:13.898 --> 00:21:17.777  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
Some kind of...
communications device

296
00:21:17.860 --> 00:21:19.779  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
implanted under his skin.

297
00:21:19.862 --> 00:21:21.322  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Remove it.

298
00:21:24.867 --> 00:21:28.120  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
Listen to me.
You and I have something in common.

299
00:21:28.204 --> 00:21:29.830  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Oh?

300
00:21:29.914 --> 00:21:32.208  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
We're both investigating disappearances.

301
00:21:32.291 --> 00:21:34.794  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
If you answer my questions,
I'll answer yours.

302
00:21:37.004 --> 00:21:40.716  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
I have an order to transfer
this patient to Division 6.

303
00:21:40.800 --> 00:21:42.176  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Division 6?

304
00:21:42.259 --> 00:21:43.385  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Neuropathology.

305
00:21:43.469 --> 00:21:45.304  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
We have reason to believe
that he's mentally ill.

306
00:21:45.930 --> 00:21:48.307  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
He's lying. How could they know that?
They've never examined me.

307
00:21:48.933 --> 00:21:50.851  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
-I'll come with you.
-I'm sorry, sir,

308
00:21:50.935 --> 00:21:52.895  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
but my orders are to bring him
for immediate treatment.

309
00:21:52.978 --> 00:21:54.897  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
This man is a suspect
in a serious crime.

310
00:21:54.980 --> 00:21:56.398  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
I'm not letting him
out of my sight.

311
00:21:56.482 --> 00:21:58.359  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
If you check the order,
you'll see it's been approved

312
00:21:58.442 --> 00:22:00.653  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
by the Director of Investigations.

313
00:22:05.908 --> 00:22:07.409  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
My real name is Chakotay.

314
00:22:07.493 --> 00:22:10.120  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
I'm an officer aboard
the Federation Starship<i> Voyager.</i>

315
00:22:10.204 --> 00:22:11.789  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Members of my crew were abducted,

316
00:22:11.872 --> 00:22:14.083  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
and their memories were altered,
and they were put to work here.

317
00:22:14.166 --> 00:22:15.501  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
I can give you names,
descriptions!

318
00:22:15.584 --> 00:22:17.211  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
[shouting] Listen to me!

319
00:22:19.880 --> 00:22:21.507  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Ah...

320
00:22:23.050 --> 00:22:24.927  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
[chuckles]

321
00:22:25.678 --> 00:22:26.846  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Smells good.

322
00:22:26.929 --> 00:22:30.348  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
Pancakes with maple syrup
are your favorite breakfast.

323
00:22:31.392 --> 00:22:34.812  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
You know, sometimes food
is like time travel.

324
00:22:34.895 --> 00:22:37.648  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
You inhale an aroma,
take a bite of something,

325
00:22:37.731 --> 00:22:40.651  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
and suddenly, bam, you're back
at the moment you first tasted it.

326
00:22:42.820 --> 00:22:44.446  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
They're good.

327
00:22:44.530 --> 00:22:46.490  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
I'm not experiencing time travel.

328
00:22:47.533 --> 00:22:48.826  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
What are you reading?

329
00:22:48.909 --> 00:22:51.120  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Personal logs.

330
00:22:51.203 --> 00:22:53.330  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
Do you remember
recording any of them?

331
00:22:54.039 --> 00:22:55.624  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
Oh, they're not mine,
they're Tom's.

332
00:22:56.792 --> 00:22:59.169  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
Those are supposed
to be private.

333
00:22:59.837 --> 00:23:01.547  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Well, he is my husband.

334
00:23:02.798 --> 00:23:04.258  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
What do they say?

335
00:23:04.341 --> 00:23:06.594  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
They're private.

336
00:23:08.386 --> 00:23:10.973  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
But the way he describes me...

337
00:23:11.056 --> 00:23:12.308  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
He loves you.

338
00:23:12.390 --> 00:23:14.852  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
I guess so.

339
00:23:16.061 --> 00:23:17.563  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
How do you feel?

340
00:23:19.940 --> 00:23:22.318  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
It's still a little foggy.

341
00:23:22.400 --> 00:23:26.155  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
That fog should lift as soon as
the Doctor finishes your treatments.

342
00:23:26.238 --> 00:23:27.531  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Yeah...

343
00:23:28.782 --> 00:23:31.619  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
but what about the guy
who recorded these logs?

344
00:23:32.369 --> 00:23:34.079  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
I've been analyzing our scans

345
00:23:34.163 --> 00:23:36.457  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
of the Quarren patrol ships
that attacked us,

346
00:23:36.540 --> 00:23:39.627  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
and I think I've devised a way
of evading their sensors.

347
00:23:39.710 --> 00:23:42.171  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
You do have a knack
for tactical planning.

348
00:23:42.254 --> 00:23:45.633  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
Hmm. That's something I've been meaning
to discuss with you.

349
00:23:45.716 --> 00:23:48.510  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
Once we've succeeded in this mission,
and I'm certain we will,

350
00:23:48.594 --> 00:23:51.889  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
I'd like you to help me program
a new medical hologram.

351
00:23:53.098 --> 00:23:55.225  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
You don't like the idea
of going back to your old job

352
00:23:55.309 --> 00:23:56.685  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
now that you've had a taste
of command.

353
00:23:56.769 --> 00:23:58.436  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
I'm a skilled officer.

354
00:23:58.520 --> 00:24:01.565  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
No offense, Doc, but that skill
was programmed into you.

355
00:24:01.649 --> 00:24:03.108  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
-Yes, but...
-I'm sure once you're back

356
00:24:03.192 --> 00:24:06.444  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
to your old self, you'll be happy
being a full-time doctor again.

357
00:24:06.528 --> 00:24:07.821  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
[beeping]

358
00:24:11.033 --> 00:24:12.868  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Commander Chakotay's hailing us.

359
00:24:14.411 --> 00:24:16.205  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
We're receiving you, sir.
Go ahead.

360
00:24:16.288 --> 00:24:18.082  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
<i>I'm having trouble</i>
<i>with my transceiver.</i>

361
00:24:18.165 --> 00:24:20.417  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
<i>This may be the last chance</i>
<i>we have to talk.</i>

362
00:24:20.501 --> 00:24:21.585  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
What's your status?

363
00:24:21.669 --> 00:24:24.672  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
I'm almost ready
to shut down the shield grid.

364
00:24:24.755 --> 00:24:27.174  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
I'm sending you
encrypted instructions.

365
00:24:27.257 --> 00:24:29.802  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
They'll tell you where
and when to enter orbit.

366
00:24:30.594 --> 00:24:33.138  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
-[Kim]<i> We have it, Commander.</i>
-Chakotay out.

367
00:24:34.390 --> 00:24:36.809  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
Well, now you know
where to find<i> Voyager...</i>

368
00:24:36.892 --> 00:24:39.812  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
I'll have three ships with me.
They won't escape again.

369
00:24:39.895 --> 00:24:43.481  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
If you'd done your job the first time,
we wouldn't have a problem now.

370
00:24:49.405 --> 00:24:51.115  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Don't you have patients to attend to?

371
00:24:51.198 --> 00:24:52.908  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Uh, yes, sir.

372
00:24:52.992 --> 00:24:54.451  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
I've been thinking.

373
00:24:54.535 --> 00:24:56.036  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
This is the second person
we've admitted

374
00:24:56.120 --> 00:24:59.456  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
with Dysphoria Syndrome in two days,
and they both work at the power plant.

375
00:24:59.540 --> 00:25:03.627  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
Maybe we should issue a health alert,
examine the rest of the workers.

376
00:25:03.711 --> 00:25:05.295  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Do you think I'm incompetent?

377
00:25:05.379 --> 00:25:07.047  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Sir?

378
00:25:08.506 --> 00:25:11.969  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
This man is in charge of personnel
at the power facility.

379
00:25:12.052 --> 00:25:14.221  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
I've informed him of the situation.

380
00:25:14.304 --> 00:25:16.223  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
We're already taking steps
to ensure the safety

381
00:25:16.306 --> 00:25:18.434  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
of all of our employees.

382
00:25:18.516 --> 00:25:21.645  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
I'm sorry to have bothered you.

383
00:25:22.438 --> 00:25:24.189  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
No need to apologize, Doctor.

384
00:25:24.273 --> 00:25:27.109  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
Your concern for your patients
is admirable,

385
00:25:27.192 --> 00:25:30.863  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
but don't worry. This man is already
responding to treatment.

386
00:25:30.946 --> 00:25:33.157  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
I expect a full recovery.

387
00:25:36.869 --> 00:25:40.247  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
Why would this Tuvok be collecting
information about his coworkers?

388
00:25:40.330 --> 00:25:43.751  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
I don't know, but the name on one
of those files is B'Elanna Torres.

389
00:25:44.960 --> 00:25:47.087  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
They both began working
at the plant on the same day,

390
00:25:47.171 --> 00:25:51.133  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
along with 136 others,
including myself.

391
00:25:51.216 --> 00:25:53.677  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
What's unusual about that?

392
00:25:53.761 --> 00:25:56.930  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
More than 100 skilled employees,
most of them the same species,

393
00:25:57.014 --> 00:25:59.141  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
acquired in a single day...

394
00:25:59.224 --> 00:26:00.893  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
during a labor shortage?

395
00:26:01.810 --> 00:26:03.062  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
You'll also note
that every one of them

396
00:26:03.145 --> 00:26:05.856  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
was processed with the Central Hospital
when they arrived.

397
00:26:05.939 --> 00:26:08.025  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
It's routine for new workers
to be examined.

398
00:26:08.108 --> 00:26:10.069  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Yes, by Quarantine Control.

399
00:26:10.152 --> 00:26:12.529  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
But everyone on this list--
all of them--

400
00:26:12.613 --> 00:26:14.948  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
were processed through Division 6.

401
00:26:15.032 --> 00:26:17.951  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
You came through Neuropathology?

402
00:26:18.035 --> 00:26:19.703  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
That's what the records indicate,

403
00:26:19.787 --> 00:26:21.747  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
but I don't remember being there.

404
00:26:23.332 --> 00:26:26.376  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
[sighs]
What do you expect me to do?

405
00:26:26.460 --> 00:26:28.170  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
You can start
by interviewing Mr. Tuvok.

406
00:26:28.253 --> 00:26:30.881  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
-You'll find him at the hospital.
-Why is he there?

407
00:26:32.007 --> 00:26:34.927  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
He became emotionally unstable.

408
00:26:35.677 --> 00:26:38.347  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
Even if I wanted to help you,
I couldn't.

409
00:26:38.430 --> 00:26:39.765  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Why not?

410
00:26:39.848 --> 00:26:43.477  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
The Director of Investigations
relieved me of duty this morning.

411
00:26:44.853 --> 00:26:47.648  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Yerid, I thought that was you.

412
00:26:47.731 --> 00:26:49.316  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
Have you found out anything
about B'Elanna?

413
00:26:49.399 --> 00:26:50.608  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
He can't assist you.

414
00:26:50.692 --> 00:26:53.362  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
He's been relieved of duty.

415
00:26:53.445 --> 00:26:54.738  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Oh.

416
00:26:54.822 --> 00:26:57.032  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
This man's also in Tuvok's file.

417
00:26:57.991 --> 00:26:59.034  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
What file?

418
00:27:00.577 --> 00:27:02.329  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Why don't you tell him?

419
00:27:02.412 --> 00:27:03.705  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Tell me what?

420
00:27:03.789 --> 00:27:07.334  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
I can't go back to the hospital
and start asking questions.

421
00:27:07.417 --> 00:27:09.086  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
I'd be reported.

422
00:27:10.628 --> 00:27:12.714  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Maybe I can help.

423
00:27:14.716 --> 00:27:16.510  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Recently, I've been...

424
00:27:17.928 --> 00:27:20.013  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
I'm a doctor.
You can trust me.

425
00:27:23.100 --> 00:27:25.643  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
I've been experiencing...

426
00:27:25.727 --> 00:27:27.813  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
some disturbing thoughts.

427
00:27:27.896 --> 00:27:29.565  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
I don't believe
it's anything serious,

428
00:27:29.647 --> 00:27:31.275  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
but I would like
to speak with someone.

429
00:27:31.358 --> 00:27:34.069  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Well, you've come to the right place.

430
00:27:39.825 --> 00:27:43.453  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
Guest Labor Code Green,
Employee 8586.

431
00:27:46.874 --> 00:27:48.584  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Hansen, Annika.

432
00:27:48.666 --> 00:27:50.752  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
You've been a patient here before.

433
00:27:50.836 --> 00:27:52.754  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Yes, when I first arrived.

434
00:27:54.423 --> 00:27:56.508  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
You were treated for
Dysphoria Syndrome.

435
00:27:57.843 --> 00:27:59.303  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
I don't recall that.

436
00:27:59.386 --> 00:28:01.305  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
These disturbing thoughts you mentioned--

437
00:28:01.388 --> 00:28:03.974  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
would you characterize them
as hallucinations?

438
00:28:04.057 --> 00:28:05.851  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
What's the cause of this syndrome?

439
00:28:05.934 --> 00:28:08.103  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
We're conducting studies
to determine that.

440
00:28:08.187 --> 00:28:09.897  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
Fortunately, we have one
of the foremost experts

441
00:28:09.980 --> 00:28:11.315  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
on the condition working here.

442
00:28:11.398 --> 00:28:12.900  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
I'd like to speak with this expert.

443
00:28:12.983 --> 00:28:14.943  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
-Well, Dr. Kadan's very busy.
-So am I.

444
00:28:15.027 --> 00:28:16.945  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
Perhaps I should return
when he's free.

445
00:28:17.029 --> 00:28:19.573  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Uh, wait here. I'll find him.

446
00:28:31.376 --> 00:28:33.837  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
[door chimes]

447
00:28:33.921 --> 00:28:35.339  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
-[door opens]
-[Jaffen] Yes?

448
00:28:35.422 --> 00:28:38.342  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
My name is Yerid.
I'm from Criminal Investigations.

449
00:28:38.425 --> 00:28:39.801  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
[Jaffen] How can I help you?

450
00:28:40.844 --> 00:28:42.179  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Kathryn Janeway?

451
00:28:42.262 --> 00:28:43.889  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Yes?

452
00:28:48.977 --> 00:28:50.771  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Do you know this man?

453
00:28:55.609 --> 00:28:56.693  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
No.

454
00:28:56.777 --> 00:28:58.111  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
I thought maybe you'd met him.

455
00:28:58.195 --> 00:28:59.613  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Why?

456
00:28:59.696 --> 00:29:01.490  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
He was found
in your former living quarters,

457
00:29:01.573 --> 00:29:05.160  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
in possession of a dermal regenerator
that you removed from the plant.

458
00:29:05.244 --> 00:29:06.495  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
I was the one who helped him.

459
00:29:06.578 --> 00:29:07.955  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Jaffen...

460
00:29:15.420 --> 00:29:18.590  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
[sighs]
He said he was from a starship,

461
00:29:18.674 --> 00:29:21.551  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
and that members of his crew
had been abducted.

462
00:29:21.635 --> 00:29:23.428  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
He was obviously lying.

463
00:29:23.512 --> 00:29:25.472  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
I want to know everything he told you.

464
00:29:29.476 --> 00:29:32.729  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
-How could she just walk out?
-She was a voluntary patient.

465
00:29:32.813 --> 00:29:35.023  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
There was no reason
for Security to stop her.

466
00:29:36.316 --> 00:29:38.568  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
She accessed 64 restricted files,

467
00:29:38.652 --> 00:29:41.655  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
all of them for people diagnosed
with Dysphoria Syndrome.

468
00:29:42.406 --> 00:29:43.949  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
According to the records,

469
00:29:44.032 --> 00:29:46.368  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
those patients were
all admitted on the same day,

470
00:29:46.451 --> 00:29:49.746  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
and you're listed as
the attending physician in every case.

471
00:29:49.830 --> 00:29:52.416  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
Oh, yes, I remember.
Quite an outbreak.

472
00:29:52.499 --> 00:29:54.251  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
You've never mentioned it.

473
00:29:54.334 --> 00:29:56.420  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Well, I'm sorry if I haven't kept you

474
00:29:56.503 --> 00:29:59.047  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
properly informed about my patients.

475
00:29:59.131 --> 00:30:01.925  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
Every one of them was discharged
to the Main Power Authority.

476
00:30:02.009 --> 00:30:04.553  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
That supervisor you were talking to--
that's where he worked.

477
00:30:04.636 --> 00:30:06.430  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
I explained that to you.

478
00:30:06.513 --> 00:30:10.017  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
I was informing him
about a potential health threat.

479
00:30:13.228 --> 00:30:15.188  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
That plant worker,
Amal Kotay--

480
00:30:15.272 --> 00:30:17.274  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
he claimed that his friends
had been abducted

481
00:30:17.357 --> 00:30:20.235  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
and put to work after having
their memories altered.

482
00:30:20.319 --> 00:30:22.279  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
What are you implying?

483
00:30:23.238 --> 00:30:25.991  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
You're making false diagnoses,

484
00:30:26.742 --> 00:30:29.703  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
selectively changing
what people remember

485
00:30:29.786 --> 00:30:31.955  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
and then sending them
to work at the power plant.

486
00:30:33.915 --> 00:30:35.667  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Very good, Doctor.

487
00:30:35.751 --> 00:30:37.461  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Why?

488
00:30:38.503 --> 00:30:40.505  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
A physician with more experience

489
00:30:40.589 --> 00:30:43.717  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
would be able to see this
in the larger context.

490
00:30:44.301 --> 00:30:47.346  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
The true public health threat
is the labor shortage,

491
00:30:47.429 --> 00:30:50.766  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
and the only cure is to find
more skilled workers.

492
00:30:50.849 --> 00:30:53.977  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
We're doctors.
We're not supposed to harm patients.

493
00:30:54.061 --> 00:30:56.897  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
We're helping them to lead
productive, happy lives.

494
00:30:56.980 --> 00:30:59.274  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
By altering their memories?

495
00:30:59.358 --> 00:31:01.902  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
The treatment I provide
improves their lives

496
00:31:01.985 --> 00:31:03.779  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
and makes them better workers.

497
00:31:03.862 --> 00:31:06.531  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
In turn, our economy benefits.

498
00:31:10.118 --> 00:31:12.537  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
You're profiting from this,
aren't you?

499
00:31:12.621 --> 00:31:17.042  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
Doesn't a physician deserve
to be compensated for his services?

500
00:31:17.125 --> 00:31:19.169  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
I'll report you.

501
00:31:19.252 --> 00:31:20.670  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
To whom?

502
00:31:20.754 --> 00:31:23.465  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
My research is funded
by the Ministry of Health.

503
00:31:25.050 --> 00:31:26.760  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Well, Criminal Investigations, then.

504
00:31:28.720 --> 00:31:30.180  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
As you may recall,

505
00:31:30.263 --> 00:31:33.600  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
the Director of Investigations
was the one who ordered

506
00:31:33.683 --> 00:31:37.938  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Amal Kotay be placed under my care.

507
00:31:40.107 --> 00:31:41.650  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Does everyone know about this?

508
00:31:41.733 --> 00:31:45.612  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
Not everyone.
Just a few trusted associates.

509
00:31:47.739 --> 00:31:52.035  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
The question is...
are you going to be one of them?

510
00:31:55.414 --> 00:31:57.457  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
[Officer] She's considered dangerous.

511
00:31:57.541 --> 00:31:59.543  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
She's never been in here.

512
00:31:59.626 --> 00:32:00.710  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
You're sure?

513
00:32:00.794 --> 00:32:03.130  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
[laughs]
I don't think I'd forget that face.

514
00:32:04.381 --> 00:32:06.800  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
If you do see her,
report it immediately.

515
00:32:06.883 --> 00:32:08.802  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
She needs to be hospitalized.

516
00:32:11.012 --> 00:32:13.807  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
[door opens, closes]

517
00:32:13.890 --> 00:32:15.642  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
It's safe now.

518
00:32:20.063 --> 00:32:21.189  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Thank you.

519
00:32:21.273 --> 00:32:25.819  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
Well, if you really want to thank me,
you can tell me what's going on.

520
00:32:25.902 --> 00:32:29.156  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
It appears this Chakotay
was telling the truth.

521
00:32:29.239 --> 00:32:32.117  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
So, uh, every worker at the plant
had their memories altered?

522
00:32:32.200 --> 00:32:33.869  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
I don't believe it's every worker.

523
00:32:33.952 --> 00:32:36.163  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
Your name didn't appear
in Dr. Kadan's patient files,

524
00:32:36.246 --> 00:32:37.706  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
but mine did.

525
00:32:37.789 --> 00:32:39.124  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
So did yours.

526
00:32:39.207 --> 00:32:41.334  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
We should report this
to the authorities.

527
00:32:41.418 --> 00:32:44.546  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
I'll need more evidence
before I start making accusations.

528
00:32:44.629 --> 00:32:48.133  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
Chakotay said he had proof
of my real identity...

529
00:32:48.633 --> 00:32:50.677  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
aboard a ship called<i> Voyager.</i>

530
00:32:50.760 --> 00:32:52.929  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
How can we locate it?

531
00:32:53.013 --> 00:32:55.182  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
When his crew contacted him,

532
00:32:55.807 --> 00:32:57.809  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
they were using...

533
00:32:57.893 --> 00:33:03.356  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
a triaxilating frequency
on a covariant subspace band.

534
00:33:03.440 --> 00:33:06.067  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
There's a subspace transponder
at the power plant.

535
00:33:09.988 --> 00:33:13.575  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
I'm going back to the plant
to try to contact this ship.

536
00:33:13.658 --> 00:33:16.369  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
I understand if you don't want
to be involved.

537
00:33:16.453 --> 00:33:19.080  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
I've been involved
from the moment I met you.

538
00:33:20.290 --> 00:33:23.251  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
If I were to return to the hospital
in your custody,

539
00:33:23.335 --> 00:33:26.213  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
it would give us an opportunity
to help Chakotay and Tuvok.

540
00:33:28.256 --> 00:33:31.718  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
I had to sedate her.
She wouldn't come voluntarily.

541
00:33:32.511 --> 00:33:34.721  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Her condition's obviously worsened.

542
00:33:34.804 --> 00:33:36.223  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
I'll treat her.

543
00:33:36.306 --> 00:33:38.975  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
There are some other patients
I'd like to interview.

544
00:33:43.313 --> 00:33:44.856  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
These people can't be disturbed.

545
00:33:51.696 --> 00:33:53.657  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
I suggest you comply.

546
00:34:00.413 --> 00:34:01.414  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
[door opens]

547
00:34:02.415 --> 00:34:03.959  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Be careful.

548
00:34:22.394 --> 00:34:24.437  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
-We're being hailed.
-[Doctor] On screen.

549
00:34:27.023 --> 00:34:28.441  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Starship Voyager...

550
00:34:28.525 --> 00:34:29.985  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Captain?

551
00:34:30.986 --> 00:34:33.280  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
<i>Why don't you just call me Kathryn?</i>

552
00:34:33.363 --> 00:34:36.783  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
Yes, ma'am.
Where's Commander Chakotay?

553
00:34:36.866 --> 00:34:38.451  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
<i>Hospitalized.</i>

554
00:34:38.535 --> 00:34:40.704  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
He told me you had proof...

555
00:34:41.496 --> 00:34:44.082  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
of who some of us really are.

556
00:34:44.165 --> 00:34:45.709  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
<i>We do.</i>

557
00:34:45.792 --> 00:34:48.503  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
You're the woman who was abducted.

558
00:34:48.587 --> 00:34:50.964  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
<i>Chakotay was supposed</i>
<i>to deactivate the shield grid,</i>

559
00:34:51.047 --> 00:34:53.758  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
<i>so we could transport you</i>
<i>and the others to safety.</i>

560
00:34:53.842 --> 00:34:55.760  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
<i>If you could find a way</i>
<i>to shut down main power,</i>

561
00:34:55.844 --> 00:34:57.554  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
<i>the shield grid will go down, too.</i>

562
00:34:57.637 --> 00:34:59.139  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
<i>Will you help us?</i>

563
00:35:00.682 --> 00:35:02.767  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
[rumbling]

564
00:35:02.851 --> 00:35:04.894  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
We're under attack.
Three ships.

565
00:35:10.609 --> 00:35:12.819  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
<i>Please, shut down the shield--</i>

566
00:35:12.902 --> 00:35:14.487  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
[beeping]

567
00:35:24.164 --> 00:35:25.498  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Jaffen?

568
00:35:29.419 --> 00:35:31.171  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Stop!

569
00:35:45.810 --> 00:35:47.771  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
[alarm blaring]

570
00:35:48.980 --> 00:35:50.148  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Don't move!

571
00:35:54.527 --> 00:35:56.655  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
[groans]

572
00:35:56.738 --> 00:35:58.657  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
[man] Stay where you are.

573
00:36:03.662 --> 00:36:04.871  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
[grunting]

574
00:36:09.959 --> 00:36:11.419  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
I hope you didn't think
I abandoned you.

575
00:36:11.503 --> 00:36:12.754  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Never occurred to me.

576
00:36:12.837 --> 00:36:15.465  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
We need to shut down
the main generators.

577
00:36:19.761 --> 00:36:21.513  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
So much for evading their sensors.

578
00:36:21.596 --> 00:36:24.766  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
The only way they could've found us
is if they knew exactly where to look.

579
00:36:27.394 --> 00:36:29.604  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Transporters are off-line.

580
00:36:32.065 --> 00:36:34.693  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
-[woman] Evacuate.
-[man] My port is shut down.

581
00:36:37.028 --> 00:36:39.280  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
We'll never get to
the generator controls.

582
00:36:41.533 --> 00:36:44.411  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
-Maybe we don't have to.
-What are you doing?

583
00:36:44.494 --> 00:36:47.288  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
If I can make the computer think
the core is going to overload,

584
00:36:47.372 --> 00:36:49.582  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
the main power should
automatically shut down.

585
00:36:49.666 --> 00:36:51.626  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
[beeping]

586
00:37:04.556 --> 00:37:07.475  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Ask them to give us some privacy.

587
00:37:07.559 --> 00:37:09.310  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
You're dismissed.

588
00:37:09.394 --> 00:37:10.395  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
[footsteps retreating]

589
00:37:11.896 --> 00:37:13.565  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Disconnect them.

590
00:37:18.319 --> 00:37:20.280  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Dr. Ravoc?

591
00:37:21.573 --> 00:37:23.074  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Why is this man here?

592
00:37:24.284 --> 00:37:25.910  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Dysphoria Syndrome.

593
00:37:25.994 --> 00:37:27.495  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
[clicking]

594
00:37:30.790 --> 00:37:32.709  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
We're losing shields.

595
00:37:32.792 --> 00:37:35.086  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Any advice from your tactical database?

596
00:37:35.170 --> 00:37:36.671  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Nothing relevant.

597
00:37:36.755 --> 00:37:38.965  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
How many escape pods
do we have left?

598
00:37:39.048 --> 00:37:40.842  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Five.

599
00:37:40.925 --> 00:37:42.385  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Stand by to eject three of them.

600
00:37:42.469 --> 00:37:44.679  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
I don't think abandoning ship
is the answer.

601
00:37:44.763 --> 00:37:46.556  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
Neither do I.
Can you create a dampening field

602
00:37:46.639 --> 00:37:48.475  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
around the briefing room
that'll mask our life signs?

603
00:37:48.558 --> 00:37:50.226  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
I believe so. Why?

604
00:37:50.310 --> 00:37:51.936  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Watch and learn.

605
00:38:00.695 --> 00:38:02.822  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
<i>Your crew's abandoned you again.</i>

606
00:38:02.906 --> 00:38:04.991  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
<i>I suggest you surrender your vessel.</i>

607
00:38:05.074 --> 00:38:08.369  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
You should realize by now that
I'm not programmed to do that.

608
00:38:17.128 --> 00:38:18.421  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Bravo, Ensign.

609
00:38:18.505 --> 00:38:20.757  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
B'Elanna, I need those transporters.

610
00:38:21.925 --> 00:38:23.635  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
You better hurry up.

611
00:38:24.302 --> 00:38:27.222  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Come on... do it.

612
00:38:28.306 --> 00:38:29.474  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
[alarm blaring]

613
00:38:29.557 --> 00:38:31.559  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
[Computer]<i> Warning.</i>
<i>Core overload detected.</i>

614
00:38:31.643 --> 00:38:33.686  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
<i>Initiating emergency shutdown.</i>

615
00:38:36.606 --> 00:38:37.982  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
[man] We've got to go!

616
00:38:46.324 --> 00:38:48.201  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Their shield grid's failing.

617
00:38:48.993 --> 00:38:50.370  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
B'Elanna?

618
00:38:50.453 --> 00:38:52.914  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Transporters are coming online... now!

619
00:39:08.721 --> 00:39:10.807  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
[Doctor]<i> ECH Log, supplemental.</i>

620
00:39:10.890 --> 00:39:13.351  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
<i>All the crew have been</i>
<i>transported back to</i> Voyager,

621
00:39:13.434 --> 00:39:15.687  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
<i>and thanks to my experience</i>
<i>with Lieutenant Torres,</i>

622
00:39:15.770 --> 00:39:17.897  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
<i>their treatment</i>
<i>is proceeding rapidly.</i>

623
00:39:17.981 --> 00:39:19.482  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
<i>While they're recovering,</i>

624
00:39:19.566 --> 00:39:22.694  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
<i>I still have a few command duties</i>
<i>left to perform.</i>

625
00:39:22.777 --> 00:39:24.112  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
If it weren't for your efforts,

626
00:39:24.195 --> 00:39:26.823  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
this whole conspiracy might
never have been uncovered.

627
00:39:27.574 --> 00:39:29.075  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
What'll happen to the workers?

628
00:39:29.158 --> 00:39:31.911  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
Well, we've identified several thousand
of Dr. Kadan's patients.

629
00:39:31.995 --> 00:39:34.289  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
Once they're treated,
they'll be repatriated.

630
00:39:34.372 --> 00:39:36.291  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
We appreciate everything you've done.

631
00:39:36.374 --> 00:39:37.959  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
This way.

632
00:39:39.627 --> 00:39:41.796  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
-[door opens]
-[sighs]

633
00:39:46.217 --> 00:39:48.136  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
<i>[laughter]</i>

634
00:39:51.180 --> 00:39:52.932  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
[laughing]

635
00:39:57.896 --> 00:39:59.981  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
[chuckling]

636
00:40:05.737 --> 00:40:07.906  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
<i>-Ooh!</i>
-[chuckles]

637
00:40:09.574 --> 00:40:11.993  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
[cartoon sound effects and music]

638
00:40:19.751 --> 00:40:21.836  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
What's that for?

639
00:40:21.920 --> 00:40:23.963  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
For taking care of me,

640
00:40:24.047 --> 00:40:26.424  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
even when you didn't know
who I was.

641
00:40:30.762 --> 00:40:32.347  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Ow!

642
00:40:32.430 --> 00:40:33.723  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
What was that for?

643
00:40:33.806 --> 00:40:35.934  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Flirting with your customers.

644
00:40:36.935 --> 00:40:39.354  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
I was a victim of mind control.

645
00:40:40.772 --> 00:40:42.357  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Mm-hmm.

646
00:40:56.079 --> 00:40:58.247  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
I can see why
you'd rather live here.

647
00:40:59.040 --> 00:41:00.667  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
I'd offer you a position.

648
00:41:00.750 --> 00:41:03.711  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
I could always use
another skilled engineer.

649
00:41:04.796 --> 00:41:06.506  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
But as the Captain...

650
00:41:07.590 --> 00:41:11.052  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
it wouldn't really be
appropriate for me to...

651
00:41:11.135 --> 00:41:13.388  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
Fraternize with a member
of your crew.

652
00:41:15.515 --> 00:41:18.559  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
Well, at least my memories
weren't tampered with.

653
00:41:18.643 --> 00:41:20.395  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
According to the medical reports,

654
00:41:20.478 --> 00:41:23.439  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
I really did come to Quarra
looking for a better life,

655
00:41:23.523 --> 00:41:26.359  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
and now that I've been promoted,
I guess I've succeeded.

656
00:41:26.442 --> 00:41:28.361  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Promotion?

657
00:41:28.444 --> 00:41:31.990  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
They had to replace
our shift supervisor.

658
00:41:32.073 --> 00:41:35.910  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
Something about
acquiring workers illegally.

659
00:41:35.994 --> 00:41:39.163  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
Congratulations.
You deserve it.

660
00:41:39.998 --> 00:41:42.417  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
I thought you might
like these back...

661
00:41:42.500 --> 00:41:45.670  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
to remind you
of our time together.

662
00:41:46.462 --> 00:41:50.091  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
I won't need souvenirs
to remember you.

663
00:42:14.240 --> 00:42:15.742  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Captain on the Bridge!

664
00:42:34.218 --> 00:42:35.511  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Ready to go?

665
00:42:36.888 --> 00:42:39.307  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
It may not have been real,
Chakotay,

666
00:42:39.390 --> 00:42:40.933  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
but it felt like home.

667
00:42:42.018 --> 00:42:44.270  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
If you hadn't come after me,

668
00:42:44.353 --> 00:42:47.440  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
I never would've known
that I had another life.

669
00:42:47.523 --> 00:42:49.859  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Are you sorry I showed up?

670
00:42:52.987 --> 00:42:54.614  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Not for a second.

671
00:42:57.784 --> 00:42:59.827  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Resume course, Mr. Paris.

672
00:42:59.911 --> 00:43:01.496  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
[Paris] Aye, sir.

